oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Frank Bittinger
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A black and white photograph of Mr. & Mrs. Frank Bittinger and their daughter, Martha, of Kingston Springs, Tenn., who have practiced the Home Food Supply principle for more than thirty years. They stand in front of a house, with porch swing, and a tree.
The Home Food Supply Program was a war-relief program instituted by the administration of Gov. Prentice Cooper.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
